The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and computer networks (cs.NI). The use of closure operators and matroids also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the solvability of network coding instances, which can be seen as a computational problem (cs.CC). Finally, the paper introduces new concepts and generalizations related to network coding, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
